    <naif_host_id>ODY</naif_host_id>
    <description>The Mars Odyssey spacecraft, built by Lockheed Martin, is equipped with various instruments that collect data during its Mars missions. This data is transmitted to Earth's NASA Deep Space Network (DSN) for analysis. The spacecraft consists of two modules: an equipment module housing scientific instruments and an equipment module housing propulsion components. It features a command and data handling system based on a RAD6000 computer, a telecommunications system with multiple antennas for communication with Earth and Mars landers, and a propulsion system with a main engine and small thrusters. Power is generated via solar panels, and thermal control mechanisms ensure operational temperatures are maintained. The DSN, managed by the Jet Propulsion Laboratory, facilitates two-way communication using a series of antennas located globally to support spacecraft exploration of the solar system.</description>
